valveBRun : BOOL; (* Valve B Run Command *)
valveCRun : BOOL; (* Valve C Run Command *)
valveDRun : BOOL; (* Valve D Run Command *)
mixMotorRun : BOOL; (* Mixing Motor Run Command *)
Implementation Requirements:
- Implement the emergency stop logic to ensure that all equipment stops immediately when the emergency stop signal is triggered.
- In manual mode, manually control the start/stop of valves and the mixing motor.
- For example, pressing the valve A start button (triggering a rising edge) causes valve A to run (valveARun=TRUE); pressing the valve A start button again (triggering a rising edge) stops valve A (valveARun=FALSE).
- In automatic mode, implement the following control logic based on the process flow:
  - Press the autoStart button to start the automatic process, first opening valve A.
  - When the liquid level sensor reaches 50cm, close valve A and open valve B.
  - When the liquid level sensor reaches 80cm, close valve B.
  - Based on #processMode:
- If #processMode=false, start the mixing motor; after receiving the mixing complete signal, stop the mixing motor, open valve D, and the automatic process ends.
- If #processMode=true, open valve C; when the liquid level sensor reaches 100cm, close valve C, start the mixing motor; after receiving the mixing complete signal, stop the mixing motor, open valve D, and the automatic process ends.

FUNCTION_BLOCK MaterialMixing
VAR_INPUT
estop : BOOL;
opeMode : BOOL;
valveAStart : BOOL;
valveBStart : BOOL;
valveCStart : BOOL;
valveDStart : BOOL;
mixMotorStart : BOOL;
autoStart : BOOL;
processMode : BOOL;
levelSensor : INT;
mixMotorComplete : BOOL;
END_VAR
VAR_OUTPUT
valveARun : BOOL;
valveBRun : BOOL;
valveCRun : BOOL;
valveDRun : BOOL;
mixMotorRun : BOOL;
END_VAR
VAR
previousValveAStart : BOOL := FALSE;
previousValveBStart : BOOL := FALSE;
previousValveCStart : BOOL := FALSE;
previousValveDStart : BOOL := FALSE;
previousMixMotorStart : BOOL := FALSE;
previousAutoStart : BOOL := FALSE;
END_VAR

